<br>
Aria of Innocence is &quot;Slot 1: Decrease Curse counter by Slot 2, 2: Decrease Curse counter by 2&quot;, and is wind based.<br>
<br>
So the formula for the number of counters removed is counters removed by the first slot + number removed by the second slot.<br>
Which is [2 * Wind mod] (rounded down) + [2 * Wind mod] (rounded down).<br>
<br>
Examples: <br>
<br>
Muramite flute off PSM + IIM is a 4.0 wind mod.  This removes 16 counters per cast.  I know of no higher wind mod.<br>
<br>
Muramite flute off PSM + IM3 is a 3.8 wind mod.  This removes 7 + 7 = 14 curse counters.  <br>
I believe it was Reed who confirmed it does not remove 15 curse counters, which is what 2*wind mod*2 (rounded down) would give you.<br>
<br>
Flute of Torment + IM3 is a 3.4 mod, so it removes 12 curse counters.<br>
<br>
etc.<br>
<br>
